hinks has been much underrated: the tales (paramythia) and the songs of love and marriage.In exploring the relationship between speech and ritual, Alexiou not only takes the Greek language into account but also invokes the neurological disorder of autism, drawing on clinical studies and her own experience as the mother of autistic identical twin sons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aByzantine literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aGreek literature, Moderny1453-1800xHistory and criticism. 0aGreek literature, Moderny19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMetaphor. 0aMythology in literature. 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172049940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501720499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501720499/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles